  "prompt": "How can you tell who has viewed Instagram videos?",
  "response": "Unfortunately, Instagram's privacy policies limit the information you can see about who has viewed your videos. Here's a breakdown:\n\n**For Regular Instagram Videos (posted to your feed):**\n\n*   **You can only see the number of views.** Instagram doesn't provide a list of specific usernames that have watched the video.\n*   **You can see who \"liked\" or \"commented\" on the video.** Likes and comments are visible indicators of engagement, but they don't necessarily mean someone watched the whole video.\n\n**For Instagram Stories Videos:**\n\n*   **You CAN see a list of viewers within 24 hours.** After you post a Story, you can swipe up on the screen while viewing it. A list of usernames who viewed each segment of your story will appear.\n*   **After 24 hours, the list of viewers disappears.** You will no longer be able to see who viewed your story.\n\n**For Instagram Reels:**\n\n*   **You can only see the number of views.** Similar to regular feed videos, Reels do not provide a list of individual viewers.\n*   **You can see who \"liked\" or \"commented\" on the reel.** But not view counts.\n\n**For Instagram Live Videos:**\n\n*   **You can see the number of live viewers at the top of the screen while you are broadcasting.**\n*   **After the Live video ends (and if you choose to share it to your Story), you can see the viewers just like a normal Story for the next 24 hours.**\n\n**Summary Chart:**\n\n| Feature        | See # of Views | See List of Viewers | Time Limit for Viewer List |\n|----------------|----------------|-----------------------|----------------------------|\n| Feed Video     | Yes            | No                    | N/A                        |\n| Story Video    | Yes            | Yes (24h)             | 24 Hours                   |\n| Reel           | Yes            | No                    | N/A                        |\n| Live Video     | Yes            | Yes (24h if shared)   | 24 Hours (if shared)       |\n\n**Important Considerations:**\n\n*   **Private Accounts:** If your account is private, only your approved followers can see your videos. Therefore, the viewers will be limited to those who follow you.\n*   **Third-Party Apps:** Be extremely cautious of any third-party apps claiming to show you who has viewed your Instagram videos. These apps are often scams, violate Instagram's terms of service, and can compromise your account security. It is highly advised to avoid them.\n\n**In conclusion, Instagram intentionally limits access to individual viewer information to protect user privacy.** You can see the overall number of views for most video formats and a list of viewers for Stories and Live videos (within a 24-hour window). However, you cannot typically see a specific list of who watched regular feed videos or Reels.\n",
